<subSubSection id="4189652DFFE26928FF236CD7D6EDAB71" pageId="12" pageNumber="453" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="092C36A6FFE26928FF236CD7D6EDAB71" blockId="12.[151,1437,153,395]" pageId="12" pageNumber="453">
<emphasis id="3BE7EAB4FFE26928FF236CD7D409AA81" bold="true" box="[199,308,153,179]" pageId="12" pageNumber="453">Remarks</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName id="CE934D25FFE26928FEA66CD7D76FAA81" authority="Santos-Silva &amp; Nascimento &amp; Kozlov, 2019" authorityName="Santos-Silva &amp; Nascimento &amp; Kozlov" authorityYear="2019" box="[322,594,153,179]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Hyperplatys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="453" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ushveridzei" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="3BE7EAB4FFE26928FEA66CD7D76FAA81" box="[322,594,153,179]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="453">Hyperplatys ushveridzei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="20D457CFFFE26928FDBC6CD7D792AA81" box="[600,687,153,179]" pageId="12" pageNumber="453" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="CE934D25FFE26928FCA46CD4D1B0AA81" authority="Haldeman, 1847" authorityName="Haldeman" authorityYear="1847" box="[832,1165,153,179]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Hyperplatys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="453" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="maculata">
<emphasis id="3BE7EAB4FFE26928FCA46CD4D6F7AA81" box="[832,970,153,179]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="453">H. maculata</emphasis>
Haldeman, 1847
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="CE934D25FFE26928FB2C6CD4D5EFAAE5" authority="Casey, 1913" authorityName="Casey" authorityYear="1913" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Hyperplatys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="453" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="montana">
<emphasis id="3BE7EAB4FFE26928FB2C6CD4D071AA81" box="[1224,1356,154,179]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="453">H. montana</emphasis>
Casey, 1913
</taxonomicName>
, but differs by the lateral tubercles of the prothorax slightly directed backward (strongly in 
<taxonomicName id="CE934D25FFE26928FB046CF0D051AAE5" authorityName="Haldeman" authorityYear="1847" box="[1248,1388,189,215]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Hyperplatys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="453" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="maculata">
<emphasis id="3BE7EAB4FFE26928FB046CF0D051AAE5" box="[1248,1388,189,215]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="453">H. maculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="CE934D25FFE26928FF736CACD426AAC9" authorityName="Casey" authorityYear="1913" box="[151,283,226,251]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Hyperplatys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="453" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="montana">
<emphasis id="3BE7EAB4FFE26928FF736CACD426AAC9" box="[151,283,226,251]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="453">H. montana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), and absence of oblique band with sparse pubescence on posterior third (present in 
<taxonomicName id="CE934D25FFE26928FB266CACD071AAC9" authorityName="Haldeman" authorityYear="1847" box="[1218,1356,225,251]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Hyperplatys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="453" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="maculata">
<emphasis id="3BE7EAB4FFE26928FB266CACD071AAC9" box="[1218,1356,225,251]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="453">H. maculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="CE934D25FFE26928FA656CACD5C4AB2D" authorityName="Casey" authorityYear="1913" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Hyperplatys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="453" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="montana">
<emphasis id="3BE7EAB4FFE26928FA656CACD5C4AB2D" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="453">H. montana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). It is also similar to 
<taxonomicName id="CE934D25FFE26928FE076D48D6B1AB2D" authority="(Bates, 1885)" authorityName="Bates" authorityYear="1885" baseAuthorityName="Bates" baseAuthorityYear="1885" box="[483,908,260,287]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Hyperplatys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="453" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="pusillus" subSpecies="nigrisparsus">
<emphasis id="3BE7EAB4FFE26928FE076D48D7D3AB2D" box="[483,750,261,287]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="453">H. pusillus nigrisparsus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="6D024B57FFE26928FD186D4BD6B9AB2D" author="Bates, H. W." box="[764,900,260,287]" pageId="12" pageNumber="453" pagination="249 - 436" refId="ref18173" refString="Bates, H. W. (1885) Biologia Centrali-Americana, Insecta, Coleoptera, suppl. to Longicornia. Vol. 5. Bernard Quaritch Limited, London, 188 pp. [pp. 249 - 436]" type="book chapter" year="1885">Bates, 1885</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, but differs by the absence of wide macula with sparse pubescence on posterior third (present in 
<taxonomicName id="CE934D25FFE26928FD506D64D6FDAB71" baseAuthorityName="Bates" baseAuthorityYear="1885" box="[692,960,297,323]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Hyperplatys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="453" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="pusillus" subSpecies="nigrisparsus">
<emphasis id="3BE7EAB4FFE26928FD506D64D6FDAB71" box="[692,960,297,323]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="453">H. pusillus nigrisparsus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="4189652DFFE26928FF236D03D057ABB9" pageId="12" pageNumber="453" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="092C36A6FFE26928FF236D03D057ABB9" blockId="12.[151,1437,153,395]" pageId="12" pageNumber="453">
<emphasis id="3BE7EAB4FFE26928FF236D03D473AB55" bold="true" box="[199,334,333,359]" pageId="12" pageNumber="453">Etymology.</emphasis>
The new species is dedicated Giya Shalvovich Ushveridze (
<collectingRegion id="CB57F844FFE26928FC016D03D175AB55" box="[997,1096,333,359]" country="Russia" name="Moscow" pageId="12" pageNumber="453">Moscow</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry id="71847636FFE26928FBB66D03D19CAB5A" box="[1106,1185,333,360]" name="Russia" pageId="12" pageNumber="453">Russia</collectingCountry>
), a collector of insects. He is a personal friend of the third author, who in this way wishes to express his gratitude and respect for him.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
